JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa is calling on politicians to stop using gender-based violence for political gain. WATCH: President Ramaphosa replies to Sona Debate On Tuesday, EFF leader, Julius Malema accused Ramaphosa of having abused his ex-wife after ANC MP Boy Mamabolo, accused Malema of abusing his wife. Ramaphosa apologised to Malema for Mamabolo's comments. Ramaphosa in his reply, reiterated that apartheid was indeed a crime against humanity. Last week, former President FW de Klerk was criticised by EFF MPs for claiming otherwise. Several anti-apartheid groups and foundations lashed out at De Klerk and he apologised earlier this week. Ramaphosa was replying to the debate on his State of the Nation Address.